Description:
Sponge varying from thin to thick encrusting or massive (1.5 × 1.0 × 
0.2 cm
) (
Fig. 4A–C
). Consistency is compressible. Cormus is formed by irregular and tightly anastomosed tubes (
0.3−0.5 mm
). Watercollecting tubes are present. Granular cells were not observed. Aquiferous system is asconoid.

1. Triactines I (large): Regular (equiangular and equiradiate). Actines are conical, straight, or slightly undulated with blunt tips (
Fig. 4E
).

2. Triactines II (small): Regular (equiangular and equiradiate). Actines are conical, straight, with blunt or sharp tips (
Fig. 4F
).
